package src
  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    AVLTree
    An AVL Tree class for storing stock data The AVL tree is a self-balancing binary search tree, it maintains the property that the height of the left and right subtrees of any node differ by at most one
    FileGeneretor
    A class for generating a file with random operations The file will contain a specified number of operations, each operation will be one of the following: - ADD: Add a new stock to the AVL tree - REMOVE: Remove a stock from the AVL tree - SEARCH: Search for a stock in the AVL tree - UPDATE: Update a stock in the AVL tree
    GUIVisualization
    A class for visualizing data in a graph
    Main
    A class for generating a file with random operations and performing a performance analysis
    Stock
    Stock class Represents a stock with symbol, price, volume, and market capitalization
    StockDataManager
    A class for managing stock data with AVL Tree
